  "content": {
    "visible_text": "Blue Belt The color blue is a very cool color. It is the color of the sky, and it passively surrounds the Earth and trees. The Blue Belt student learns about the power of air, and how to pull what you need from the air around you. Learning to fly is the key to finding out about this color, and the Blue Belt soars to new heights in their training. The cardinal element of the blue belt is air. From the air we get the oxygen we breath. Our breathing gives us life. As a Blue Belt we should begin to study our breathing and learn to control it. This can keep us calm in difficult situations or help us generate tremendous power. This is also a time for the student to begin refining their technique, and to contemplate on what they have been learning since they were a white belt. As a Blue Belt you should no longer be “going through the steps” of your forms. You have trained long and hard, you should now aspire to fully understand your techniques and stances. You demonstrate this knowledge by doing your forms with grace and power. But to do this, you will first have to find your breath. Blue Belt Curriculum Techniques Kids Form (Terra Moto) Teens Form (Attitude) Hubud Blue Belt One Stripe Curriculum Techniques Kids One-Steps 16–18 Teens One-Steps BB 1–3 Blue Belt Two Stripes Curriculum Techniques Kids Form (Riverbed) Teens Form (Waterfall) Standing Grappling Blue Belt Three Stripes Curriculum Techniques Kids One-Steps 19–21 Teens One-Steps BB 4–6 Spontaneous One-Steps Reviews Facebook Community Dojo Quantum Martial Arts is a registered 501(c)(3) nonprofit in the State of California, and we thrive on the generosity of people like you. All donations are tax-deductible. Quantum’s tax ID number is 26-1534597. No donation is too small, or too large. Whether it’s $20 or $20,000, every cent will be hugely appreciated and put to good use. Support Our Kids Donate now to support our youth scholarship program which allows families in need to train at reduced cost. We believe investment in our community involves investing in our youth. Our Sister Schools Our Seattle Dojo has served thousands of students since opening on Capitol Hill in 1995, and currently offers youth and adult classes in the Central District. Our Portland Dojo was established in 2020, and currently offers youth and adult classes in Southeast Portland. A WordPress.com Website .",
